race.description: Steelforce Arc Metal Centre Maiden Handicap
race.comment: RAVE ABOUT IT (6) was backed from $4.80 into $3.60 on debut last start over this distance at Warwick Farm but after showing pace to the turn could not finish it off. Will take a lot from that run and around this tight circuit might prove tougher to catch. LIPSTICK (2) settled at the tail of a small field over 1250m at the Kensington track last time and had trouble getting involved, passing just one runner. Has only raced at the provincials once and filled a placing so this looks a more suitable assignment. NAFANUA (4) has not raced since finishing second at odds-on on debut in heavy going at Nowra in September. Two recent trial wins are a positive sign. Expecting a bright start to this second prep. The Waterhouse/Bott first starter HELLUVA KISS (5) is a half-sister to the stakes winner The Nephew. Has showed ability at the trials and this stable's youngsters must always be watched carefully. COSMIC EAGLE (11) hit the ground running in the maiden campaign and is in the mix first-up.
